(
<figureCitation id="133EC4B2C3133743FF0D44FBFF5F777D" box="[159,242,1777,1803]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1792,1817]" captionTargetBox="[280,1307,181,1767]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[280,1307,181,1767]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 19. Alvania spp. A, B. Alvania canariensis (d’Orbigny, 1840), Candelara la Caleta, Tenerife, Canary Island (Spain), height 2 mm (BA). C, D. Alvania sp. aff. canariensis (d’Orbigny, 1840), Gando Bay, Gran Canaria, Canary Islands (Spain), height 1. 85 mm (BA). E, F. Alvania canariensis (d’Orbigny, 1840), Monterosato coll. ex Mac Andrew coll., MCZR-M-30074, Canary Islands (Spain), height 1.8 mm with original label. G, H. Alvania angioyi vanAartsen, 1982, Biscoitos, Terceira (Azores), 1 m depth, height 1.7 mm (JT, JDO). I–K. Alvania sp., Monterosato coll. ex Mac Andrew coll., MCZR-M-30074, Azores, height 2 mm. L–P. Alvania grancanariensis Segers, 1999, Maspalomas, Gran Canaria, Canary Islands (Spain) height 1.7 mm (L: JT, JDO), 1.7 mm (M: JT, JDO), 1.85 mm (N–P: JT, JDO)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3773019" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3773019/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="447">Figs 19</figureCitation>
I–K)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31F8BBCC3133743FF054532FA357725" box="[151,1432,1848,1875]" pageId="32" pageNumber="447" type="materials_examined">
