<subSubSection id="C31F8BBCC3133745FF554557FEE2711E" lastPageId="38" lastPageNumber="453" pageId="32" pageNumber="447" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BBAD837C3133745FF554557FEE2711E" blockId="32.[151,1436,1848,1984]" lastBlockId="38.[151,1436,153,360]" lastPageId="38" lastPageNumber="453" pageId="32" pageNumber="447">
<emphasis id="B9710425C3133743FF554557FE967701" bold="true" box="[199,315,1885,1911]" pageId="32" pageNumber="447">Remarks.</emphasis>
The single shell examined (
<figureCitation id="133EC4B2C3133743FDE84557FD647701" box="[634,713,1885,1911]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1792,1817]" captionTargetBox="[280,1307,181,1767]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[280,1307,181,1767]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 19. Alvania spp. A, B. Alvania canariensis (d’Orbigny, 1840), Candelara la Caleta, Tenerife, Canary Island (Spain), height 2 mm (BA). C, D. Alvania sp. aff. canariensis (d’Orbigny, 1840), Gando Bay, Gran Canaria, Canary Islands (Spain), height 1. 85 mm (BA). E, F. Alvania canariensis (d’Orbigny, 1840), Monterosato coll. ex Mac Andrew coll., MCZR-M-30074, Canary Islands (Spain), height 1.8 mm with original label. G, H. Alvania angioyi vanAartsen, 1982, Biscoitos, Terceira (Azores), 1 m depth, height 1.7 mm (JT, JDO). I–K. Alvania sp., Monterosato coll. ex Mac Andrew coll., MCZR-M-30074, Azores, height 2 mm. L–P. Alvania grancanariensis Segers, 1999, Maspalomas, Gran Canaria, Canary Islands (Spain) height 1.7 mm (L: JT, JDO), 1.7 mm (M: JT, JDO), 1.85 mm (N–P: JT, JDO)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3773019" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3773019/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="447">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
I–K) was in the same lot with several shells of 
<taxonomicName id="4C05A3B4C3133743FB724557FA2C7701" baseAuthorityName="d'Orbigny" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[1248,1409,1885,1911]" class="Gastropoda" family="Rissoidae" genus="Alvania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="32" pageNumber="447" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="canariensis">
<emphasis id="B9710425C3133743FB724557FA2C7701" box="[1248,1409,1885,1911]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="447">A. canariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a species ranging from 
<collectingRegion id="49C116D5C3133743FE15458BFD8077ED" box="[391,557,1921,1947]" country="Spain" name="Canarias" pageId="32" pageNumber="447">Canary Islands</collectingRegion>
to Selvagens and Madera. We can, therefore, only guess an origin from 
<collectingRegion id="49C116D5C3133743FAD9458BFF4B77C9" country="Spain" name="Canarias" pageId="32" pageNumber="447">Canary Islands</collectingRegion>
(considering that Mac Andrew studied particulary that fauna). The shell is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C05A3B4C3133743FB5345AFFA9E77C9" authority="Amati &amp; Appolloni &amp; Giulio &amp; Scuderi &amp; Smriglio &amp; Oliverio, 2020" authorityName="Amati &amp; Appolloni &amp; Giulio &amp; Scuderi &amp; Smriglio &amp; Oliverio" authorityYear="2020" box="[1217,1331,1957,1983]" class="Gastropoda" family="Rissoidae" genus="Alvania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="32" pageNumber="447" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pizzinii" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B9710425C3133743FB5345AFFA9E77C9" box="[1217,1331,1957,1983]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="447">A. pizzinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9710425C3133743FAAE45AFFAD077C9" bold="true" box="[1340,1405,1957,1983]" pageId="32" pageNumber="447">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A242B95EC3133743FAAE45AFFAD077C9" box="[1340,1405,1957,1983]" pageId="32" pageNumber="447" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in the angled outline and the wide subsutural ramp devoid of spiral sculpture. It differs by the semitransparent whitish colouration, with small brownish spots on the periphery 
<emphasis id="B9710425C3153745FC9A42B4FCB270A1" box="[776,799,190,215]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="453">vs</emphasis>
translucent yellowish with large quadrangular subsutural brownish blotches (or monochrome yellowish-orangeish or brownish) in 
<taxonomicName id="4C05A3B4C3153745FC7042EBFBF8708D" authorityName="Amati &amp; Appolloni &amp; Giulio &amp; Scuderi &amp; Smriglio &amp; Oliverio" authorityYear="2020" box="[994,1109,225,251]" class="Gastropoda" family="Rissoidae" genus="Alvania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="38" pageNumber="453" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pizzinii">
<emphasis id="B9710425C3153745FC7042EBFBF8708D" box="[994,1109,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="453">A. pizzinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It also resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C05A3B4C3153745FAA042EBFE827169" authority="Gofas (2007)" authorityName="Gofas" authorityYear="2007" class="Gastropoda" family="Rissoidae" genus="Alvania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="38" pageNumber="453" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="suroiti">
<emphasis id="B9710425C3153745FAA042EBFA31708D" box="[1330,1436,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="453">A. suroiti</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF94A5C6C3153745FF05430FFE827169" author="Gofas, S." box="[151,303,261,287]" pageId="38" pageNumber="453" pagination="779 - 885" refId="ref26548" refString="Gofas, S. (2007) Rissoidae (Mollusca: Gastropoda) from northeast Atlantic seamounts. Journal of Natural History, 41 (13 - 16), 779 - 885. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930701298085" type="journal article" year="2007">Gofas (2007)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, a deep-water species from the Azores (
<quantity id="4CFD75D2C3153745FD62430FFCDC7169" box="[752,881,261,287]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.75" metricValueMax="4.8" metricValueMin="4.7" pageId="38" pageNumber="453" unit="m" value="475.0" valueMax="480.0" valueMin="470.0">470–480 m</quantity>
depth), which differs in the lack of a distinct microsculpture on both the protoconch and the teleoconch (whereas this shell has distinct spiral sculpture visible on the protoconch).
</paragraph>
